abstract: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention officials cease cautioning pregnant women to avoid Miami's Wynwood arts district amid Zika concerns; say aerial pesticide spraying has killed mosquitoes that carry virus.

headline.print_headline: Officials Relax Zika Warning After Miami Spraying Effort
headline.main: Officials Relax Zika Warning for Pregnant Women in Miami Neighborhood

keywords.value: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
keywords.name: organizations

snippet: No new cases have been reported in the Wynwood area since early August. Pesticides have helped to kill mosquitoes there....
